<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-11T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-11T13:00:00-05:00" n="362" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/7121:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-11T20:00:00+02:00">December 11, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received December 11—3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>344. The British Ambassador told me this evening that General
                                    Wavell<note n="22" xml:id="d362fn22">Gen. Sir Archibald P.
                                    Wavell, Commanding General of British Forces in the Middle
                                    East.</note> had just advised him that the British had captured
                                Sidi Barrani.</p>
                            <p>The number of prisoners was at the time unknown but included three
                                generals.</p>
                            <p>General Wavell had further informed the Ambassador that the Italians
                                were fleeing and the British were in pursuit.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>